Greetings from *C**FI*!


The team from IIT Madras which participated in the *Lockheed Martin C-130
Payload Design challenge* having now won the High Level Design phase , are
looking to expand their team with more enthusiastic minds for the *Prototype
Development phase* of the competition. The team, consisting of research
scholars and undergraduates alike, have been awarded a research grant of *USD
60,000* by Lockheed Martin to develop their award winning payload concept
<http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/iit-madras-students-have-a-solution-for-easier-air-relief-missions/story-H4kqvndiDwAOrYQRbR4xUN.html>
for
the Indian Air Force's C-130J Super Hercules aircraft
<http://www.lockheedmartin.co.in/us/products/c130.html>, in collaboration
with their national industrial partner, TATA Advanced Systems.


Join the team in their orientation session, where they will be briefing
about the competition, their payload concept, their further plans and why
you should join the team. The application process for the selection will be
introduced and released during the session.


*PS:* The session is open to all Research scholars and undergraduate students
expect first year undergraduates !


*Lockheed Martin C-130 Payload Design Challenge:* *Orientation Session*


*Date:** Friday, 26th August 2016*

*Time:** 6:30 pm to 8:00 pm*

*Venue:** CRC* *302*


